Each year on the first Friday of June, people all over the world head over to a bakery to buy and indulge in their favourite doughnuts to celebrate the delicious treat, and to honour the American Army Lassies who served doughnuts to soldiers during WWI.  Here are some fun facts about doughnuts shared by UberEats, which you may not know about: In celebration of National Doughnut Day, order in some delicious doughnuts from your favourite doughnut store, or recreate these simple homemade sugar doughnuts and gift some to your closed friends and family as tribute to the Army Lassies. ALSO READ: Recipe of the day: Creamy chicken and mushroom linguine For the yeast  For the dough  This recipe was found on simplyhomecooked.com